==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Carbonaro
<hw>Car`bo*na"ro</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Carbonari</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[It., a coal man.]</ety>
<def>A member of a secret political association in Italy, organized in
the early part of the nineteenth century for the purpose of changing the
government into a republic.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ The origin of the <xex>Carbonari</xex> is uncertain, but
the society is said to have first met, in 1808, among the charcoal
burners of the mountains, whose phraseology they adopted.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Carbonatation</ent>⟦br⟧
